  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Shelter and NFI assistance to conflict affected population in North East Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IOM aims to continue the provision of direct assistance to 9,000 IDPs and returnees affected the heavy rains and flooding in North East Nigeria through: a) the distribution of Emergency Shelters (ES) kits, b) the distribution of Reinforcement Kits and c) the distribution of community drainage and site maintenance kits and d) the distribution of NFI kits. The selection of the areas of intervention has been done based on CCCM / ESampNFI sector prioritization and IOM&#x2019;s presence in the ground.</narrative>
  </description>
